-	Create Heroku and Github accounts individually.
-	Heroku --> Create new app --> select region as Europe -->...connect Heroku app to Github repo.
-	Enable automatic deploys.
-	 Heroku --> App --> Settings --> Domain name --> type in [unique domain name].codeguild.co --> Add Domain. Visit the domain to see the blog.

Github is a version control system that uses a repository to store all the files for a project i.e. my code; Heroku is a cloud-based server which essentially builds the app by hosting it.
